trans-unit.source: Represents an Azure Active Directory object.
trans-unit.target: Represents an Azure Active Directory object.

trans-unit.source: This topic provides descriptions of the properties and navigation properties of the <system>DirectoryObject</system> entity type.
trans-unit.target: This topic provides descriptions of the properties and navigation properties of the <system>DirectoryObject</system> entity type.

trans-unit.source: The <system>DirectoryObject</system> type is the base type for most of the other directory entity types.
trans-unit.target: The <system>DirectoryObject</system> type is the base type for most of the other directory entity types.

trans-unit.source: <embeddedLabel>Namespace</embeddedLabel>: Microsoft.DirectoryServices for version 1.5 and newer, Microsoft.WindowsAzure.ActiveDirectory for versions prior to 1.5.
trans-unit.target: <embeddedLabel>Namespace</embeddedLabel>: Microsoft.DirectoryServices for version 1.5 and newer, Microsoft.WindowsAzure.ActiveDirectory for versions prior to 1.5.

trans-unit.source: The <system>DirectoryObject</system> entity type is defined as follows:
trans-unit.target: The <system>DirectoryObject</system> entity type is defined as follows:

trans-unit.source: The time at which the directory object was deleted.
trans-unit.target: The time at which the directory object was deleted.

trans-unit.source: It only applies to those directory objects which can be restored.
trans-unit.target: It only applies to those directory objects which can be restored.

trans-unit.source: Currently it is only supported for deleted <link xlink:href="80e0ebce-d409-4f71-81ee-ed006b882108" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Application</link> objects; all other entities return <languageKeyword>null</languageKeyword> for this property.
trans-unit.target: Currently it is only supported for deleted <link xlink:href="80e0ebce-d409-4f71-81ee-ed006b882108" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Application</link> objects; all other entities return <languageKeyword>null</languageKeyword> for this property.

trans-unit.source: A Guid that is the unique identifier for the object; for example, 12345678-9abc-def0-1234-56789abcde.
trans-unit.target: A Guid that is the unique identifier for the object; for example, 12345678-9abc-def0-1234-56789abcde.

trans-unit.source: A string that identifies the object type.
trans-unit.target: A string that identifies the object type.

trans-unit.source: For example, for groups the value is always “Group”.
trans-unit.target: For example, for groups the value is always “Group”.

trans-unit.source: The directory objects that were created by the current object.
trans-unit.target: The directory objects that were created by the current object.

trans-unit.source: The directory object that that this object was created on behalf of.
trans-unit.target: The directory object that that this object was created on behalf of.

trans-unit.source: Returns a user or a contact.
trans-unit.target: Returns a user or a contact.

trans-unit.source: Users and contacts that report to this object.
trans-unit.target: Users and contacts that report to this object.

trans-unit.source: Objects that are members of this object.
trans-unit.target: Objects that are members of this object.

trans-unit.source: On groups, returns contacts, users, and groups.
trans-unit.target: On groups, returns contacts, users, and groups.

trans-unit.source: On roles, returns users and service principals.
trans-unit.target: On roles, returns users and service principals.

trans-unit.source: Objects that this object is a member of.
trans-unit.target: Objects that this object is a member of.

trans-unit.source: Valid on contacts, groups, service principals, and users.
trans-unit.target: Valid on contacts, groups, service principals, and users.

trans-unit.source: On users, returns groups and roles.
trans-unit.target: On users, returns groups and roles.

trans-unit.source: For example, if User A is a member of Group B and Group B is a member of Group C, the memberOf property on User A will not return Group C.
trans-unit.target: For example, if User A is a member of Group B and Group B is a member of Group C, the memberOf property on User A will not return Group C.

trans-unit.source: The directory objects that are owned by the current object.
trans-unit.target: The directory objects that are owned by the current object.

trans-unit.source: The directory objects that are owners of the current object.
trans-unit.target: The directory objects that are owners of the current object.

trans-unit.source: The owners are a set of non-admin users who are allowed to modify this object.
trans-unit.target: The owners are a set of non-admin users who are allowed to modify this object.

trans-unit.source: Not all navigation properties are necessarily valid on the entity types that inherit from <embeddedLabel>DirectoryObject</embeddedLabel>.
trans-unit.target: Not all navigation properties are necessarily valid on the entity types that inherit from <embeddedLabel>DirectoryObject</embeddedLabel>.

trans-unit.source: The full set of operations that are supported on directory objects are the following (the HTTP method used for each is in parentheses): Create (POST), Read (GET), Update (PATCH), and Delete (DELETE).
trans-unit.target: The full set of operations that are supported on directory objects are the following (the HTTP method used for each is in parentheses): Create (POST), Read (GET), Update (PATCH), and Delete (DELETE).

trans-unit.source: However, not all of these operations are supported on every entity type.
trans-unit.target: However, not all of these operations are supported on every entity type.

trans-unit.source: The declared properties of directory object are read-only; they cannot be specified in create or update operations.
trans-unit.target: The declared properties of directory object are read-only; they cannot be specified in create or update operations.

trans-unit.source: In general, the principal that represents an application must be in an administrator role that has directory WRITE privileges to send PATCH, POST, PUT or DELETE requests.
trans-unit.target: In general, the principal that represents an application must be in an administrator role that has directory WRITE privileges to send PATCH, POST, PUT or DELETE requests.

trans-unit.source: It must be in a role that has directory READ privileges to send GET requests.
trans-unit.target: It must be in a role that has directory READ privileges to send GET requests.

trans-unit.source: However, the permissions required for operations on a specific entity type can be different.
trans-unit.target: However, the permissions required for operations on a specific entity type can be different.
